to the editor dr david satcher the surgeon general should be commended for drawing attention to the significant problem of obesity in this country news article dec 14 his recommendation that schools provide more healthful food options is unlikely to succeed however unless his office works with the department of agriculture to revise guidelines for the school lunch program currently the department routinely dumps surplus meat and dairy products into the program as a way to help struggling farmers these unhealthful foods clog our children 's arteries and contribute to the obesity epidemic ensuring that healthy vegetarian meals are available to all students in schools would be a great first step toward reversing the problem bernie fischlowitz roberts washington dec 14 2001

